Basic Systax of Java:
1. Object:  An concrete example of Class, have its own State and Behaviors
2. Class:   A template that indicate the Object of this Class with its State and Behaviors
3. Method:  Methods are Behaviors of the Class would like to perform, eg: calculation, changing values of variables
4. Instance Variables:  Each Object has its own Instance Variables, while the value of Instance Variables determine the State of the Object




Creating Object:
#1. Declaration: Declare a object with its Name and Type
#2. Construction: use keyword new to construct an object

    Example:
    public class Puppy{
        public Puppy(String name){
            System.out.println("Name of the dog is: "+name);
        }
    
        public static void main(String[] args){
            Puppy myPuppy = new Puppy("Tom");
        }
    }

